The K series narrow drive axles use an internal wet disc brake
configuration allowing several brake lever mounting orientations,
depending on the reduction ratio. Brake capacity is 181 or 139 lb.ft,
at 94 lb.in, of brake arm force for the K46; 432, 347 or 240 lb.ft,
at 92.6 lb. of brake arm force for the K62; 243 or 159 lb.ft, at 67.5
lb. of brake arm force for the K66; and 535 lb.ft, at 21.2 lb.ft. of
brake arm torque for the K71 transaxle.

All four K series narrow drive transaxle models use automotive-type
heat-treated bevel gears in the differential. A differential lock is
not available on the K46, but is optional on the K62, K66 and K71. A
factory set return-to-neutral mechanism is standard on the K46, K62,
K66 and K71 transaxles with foot control applications. All four narrow
drive transaxle models include a roll release mechanism.

The K46 is designed for rear-engined riders and lawn tractors. The
standard axle torque rating for the K46 is 166 lb. ft. with the standard
20 in. maximum diameter tires and a reduction ratio of 28.04:1. The axle
is also available with a 127 lb.ft. rating and 21.53:1 reduction ratio
and a maximum tire diameter of 18 in., giving travel speeds of 5.5 mph.

The K46 transaxle hydraulic pump and motor have displacements of 7.06
cc and 10.93 cc respectively. Maximum input speed is 3000 rpm through a
0.58 in. input shaft. The axle shaft diameter measures 0.75 in. Maximum
static weight capacity for the K46 transaxle is 675 lb. and its dry
weight is 27.6 lb.

All of the narrow drive transaxles use 10W 30 class CD motor oil. The K66
uses 5W 50 synthetic motor oil for ground engagement applications. The
K46 has an oil capacity of 0.63 gallons while the K62 and K66 have a 0.66
gallon capacity and the K71 has a 1.22 gallon capacity. The K46 and K62
models use a non-changeable internal oil filter while the K66 and K71
units are available with an external changeable filter. All transaxles
are prefilled and air bled at the factory.

The K62 is designed for heavy-duty lawn tractor and yard tractor
applications. Pump and motor displacement for the K62 is 10 cc
each. Maximum input shaft speed is 3000 rpm. The input shaft has a 0.58
in. diameter and the axle shaft is 1.0 in. in diameter.

The K62 has a maximum static weight rating of 584 lb. and a dry weight of
38.6 lb. The K62 has rated axle torque of 268, 215, and 149 lb.ft. with
reduction ratios of 33.50:1, 26.90:1 and 18.65:1 using 23, 20 and 18
in. maximum diameter tires respectively. The standard axle is available
with a reduction ratio of 26.90:1 at 215 lb.ft.

